Reasoning: The paper discusses the topic of human visual attention and its modeling in computer vision, which is a common theme in the computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The use of machine learning algorithms and computational models also suggests a possible fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of large collections of data and software libraries for data usage and similarity measures suggests a possible connection with the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
